<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.77/706: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-25T19:00:00-04:00">November
                                    25, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>341. Your 398, November 23. Department agrees that Iran Government should
                            be officially informed. We regard question of public statement as matter
                            for decision by Persian Gulf Service Command. War Department
                            concurs.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>